It’s such a perfect time to beatify your smile 💋
Porcelain veneers is the #1 choice for smile enhancement by our patients. They are extremely popular for those with chipped teeth, a gap between teeth, or misshaped teeth
•
The process starts with reshaping your teeth by removing a small amount of enamel from the front and sides of the teeth. This makes room for the veneers so that teeth look natural after we place your veneers.
•
Then an impression
of your prepared teeth. 
Afterwards, together we decide on the veneers shape and shades. 
The impression is sent to a dental lab that custom-makes the porcelain veneers to fit your teeth 
•
This usually takes several days so we create you temporary veneers to wear in the meantime 
•
At your next visit, we place the veneers on the teeth to check the fit and shape. After some adjustments, the teeth are cleaned and layered with special bonding material and the veneers are placed on the tooth permanently.

As an adult, the thought of getting traditional braces may seem overwhelming or even embarrassing. Luckily, there is an alternative that can give you the straight, beautiful smile you deserve without the discomfort or stigma of metal braces. That alternative is Invisalign.

Traditional braces can be uncomfortable and even painful, especially for adults. They can also be unsightly, causing many adults to feel self-conscious about their appearance. Invisalign offers a discreet and comfortable option for straightening your teeth without the need for traditional braces.

Invisalign uses a series of clear, plastic aligners to gradually move your teeth into the correct position. These aligners are customized to fit your teeth perfectly, and they’re nearly invisible when worn. They’re also removable, which means you can eat and drink whatever you like without worrying about damaging your braces or getting food stuck in them.

Another benefit of Invisalign is that it requires fewer office visits than traditional braces. You’ll only need to visit your dentist or orthodontist every six to eight weeks for a quick checkup and to receive your new set of aligners. This means you can spend less time in the dental chair and more time enjoying your life.

In conclusion, if you’re an adult who needs braces, consider Invisalign as your solution. Not only is it more comfortable and discreet than traditional braces, but it also requires fewer office visits and allows you to maintain your normal lifestyle. Talk to your dentist or orthodontist today to see if Invisalign is right for you.

•Do you cover your teeth when you laugh or smile for photos? 

If so, you might want to consider veneers – a popular cosmetic dentistry treatment that can give you the beautiful, confident smile you deserve. 

Here are a few signs:

1️⃣ You have chips or cracks in your teeth. Veneers can cover up small imperfections and give your teeth a smooth, even appearance.

2️⃣ You have gaps between your teeth. Veneers can be used to close gaps and make your smile more symmetrical.

3️⃣ You have stubborn stains or discoloration. If your teeth are discolored and won’t respond to traditional whitening treatments, veneers can give you a bright, white smile.

4️⃣ You have misshapen or uneven teeth. Veneers can help to reshape your teeth and make them look more uniform.

Do veneers actually change the shape of your face?

Veneers are a popular cosmetic dentistry treatment that can transform your smile and give you the confidence to show off your teeth. But do veneers actually change the shape of your face? The answer is not exactly.

While veneers can improve the appearance of your teeth and make your smile look more symmetrical, they do not actually change the shape of your face. However, by improving the look of your teeth, veneers can create the illusion of a more balanced, harmonious facial appearance.

Periodontal diseases are infections and affect the gums, periodontal ligament, and alveolar bone surrounding the teeth. Infection (also known as gingivitis) is limited to the gums in its early stages, but it is a major factor for tooth loss in adulthood. If the condition is not addressed early, it might spread to other tissues, making the situation even more difficult to treat.

Reduces oral discomfort
Periodontal disease can be a source of considerable suffering. Gum disease causes gums to become painful and swollen throughout the day, and bleed during brushing. 
The symptoms of gum disease should begin to fade as periodontic treatment is delivered.
Prevents dental complications
Treatment for gum disease also aids in the prevention of more significant oral health issues. 

Due to the high level of germs in the mouth, patients with gum disease are more likely to develop tooth decay. Protecting the teeth from microorganisms gets more challenging as the gums recede. Gum recession can result in tooth loss in certain scenarios.
Bad breath is a typical indication of gum disease, as it is generated by decomposing food particles, germs, and plaque. After gum disease therapy, you will be able to experience the pleasures of naturally fresh breath once more.

There is a common misconception that teeth whitening can harm your enamel. While it is true that some teeth whitening methods can cause temporary sensitivity, there is no evidence to suggest that teeth whitening can permanently damage your enamel if done correctly and by a professional.

That being said, there are different types of teeth whitening methods available, each with their own pros and cons. Let’s compare three popular teeth whitening options: Zoom teeth whitening, home whitening kits, and Sapphire teeth whitening.

Zoom teeth whitening is a professional, in-office treatment that uses a special light to activate a bleaching gel applied to your teeth. This treatment can provide dramatic results in just one visit, making it a popular choice for people who want to see fast results. However, it can be more expensive than other whitening options, and some people may experience temporary sensitivity after the treatment.

Home whitening kits are an affordable and convenient option for teeth whitening. They typically consist of a custom-fitted tray and a bleaching gel that you apply to your teeth at home. While home whitening kits can be effective, they may take longer to achieve results than in-office treatments like Zoom, and some people may find the process to be more time-consuming and less comfortable.

Sapphire teeth whitening is another professional, in-office treatment that uses a special light to activate a whitening gel. This treatment can be gentler on teeth and gums than other whitening methods, making it a good choice for people with sensitive teeth.

Overall, the best teeth whitening option for you will depend on your individual needs and preferences. It’s always a good idea to talk to a dental professional at Envy Smile Dental Spa to discuss your options and ensure that you’re getting a safe and effective treatment.

Did you know that dentists carefully consider color when selecting dental implants? To achieve a natural-looking result, they often assess shades in daylight. Here’s why daylight matters in color matching for implants.

👉Perfect Color Matching: Dental implants should seamlessly blend with your natural teeth. Dentists evaluate factors like shade, translucency, and surface texture.

👉Daylight Advantage: Dentists prefer daylight over artificial lighting for accurate color evaluation. Artificial lights can distort shades, while daylight provides a true representation.
 
👉Lighting Conditions Matter: Teeth can appear different under various light sources. Evaluating color samples in daylight ensures a consistent and harmonious match in any environment.

👉Special Tools: Dentists use shade guides featuring tabs or chips of different colors. Comparing them to your natural teeth in daylight helps them choose the best implant shade.

👉Advanced Technology: Spectrophotometers and digital imaging devices assist in precise color matching alongside daylight and the dentist’s expertise.

👉A Seamless Smile: By considering all factors and evaluating shades in daylight, dentists create dental implants that closely match your natural teeth, restoring both function and confidence!

Experience the ultimate in teeth whitening at Envy Smile Dental Spa. Our cutting-edge technology, combined with our skilled professionals, guarantees a safe and effective treatment for a noticeably brighter smile
At our office we use Sapphire Teeth Whitening!

Sapphire teeth whitening is an advanced dental procedure designed to effectively brighten and enhance the natural color of teeth. This technique employs a specially formulated gel containing hydrogen peroxide, which, when activated by a blue light emitted from a sapphire crystal, accelerates the whitening process. The blue light technology used in this procedure helps to maximize the effectiveness of the whitening gel, ensuring a faster and more dramatic result compared to traditional methods. Furthermore, sapphire teeth whitening is known for its non-invasive nature and minimal sensitivity, making it a popular choice among individuals seeking a noticeably brighter smile without discomfort or extended downtime. The procedure is typically performed in a dental office by trained professionals, providing a safe and controlled environment for optimal results. Overall, this whitening offers a reliable and efficient solution for those looking to achieve a radiant, confident smile.

Have you heard of Invisalign?!
Invisalign is the most innovative and convenient orthodontic treatment on the market. It involves the use of clear, custom-made aligners to straighten teeth. These aligners are virtually invisible and are worn over the teeth, gradually shifting them into the desired position. Treatment can be as short as 6 months and addresses many issues from crooked teeth with crowding or spacing to an improper bite like overbites, underbites, or cross bites.
